Prerequisite

Docker installed and running
Check:

docker --version
docker ps


If Docker isn’t installed, stop here. Install Docker first.

Nexus Installation (Docker)
docker volume create nexus-data

docker run -d \
--name nexus \
-p 8081:8081 \
-v nexus-data:/nexus-data \
--restart unless-stopped \
sonatype/nexus3


That’s it. Nexus is installing in the background.

Access Nexus

Open browser:

http://<server-ip>:8081


Local machine:

http://localhost:8081


Startup takes 2–3 minutes. If you panic early, that’s on you.

Get Admin Password (MOST PEOPLE MESS THIS UP)
docker exec -it nexus cat /nexus-data/admin.password


Username: admin

Password: output of above command

Verify Container Health
docker ps

docker logs -f nexus


If it’s not running → you screwed Docker or ports.
